title: J. Palsgravii ... Ecphrasis Anglica in Comœdiam Acolasti. The Comedye of Acolastus translated into oure englysshe tongue after suche manner as chylderne are taught in the grammer schole fyrst worde for worde ... and afterwarde accordynge to the sence ... with admonitions ... for the more perfyte instructynge of the lerners, and ... brefe introductory to ... the dyvers sortes of meters, etc. Interpreted by I. Palsgrave. Lat. and Eng. B.L
